---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Blog — Mental Health & Therapy Insights | Lotus Rose Counseling"
  description="Evidence-based articles on postpartum depression, EMDR therapy, trauma recovery, grief, anxiety, and maternal mental health from the therapists at Lotus Rose Counseling in Orem, Utah."
>

  <!-- CollectionPage Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "CollectionPage",
    "name": "Lotus Rose Counseling Blog",
    "description": "Evidence-based articles on postpartum depression, EMDR therapy, trauma recovery, grief, and maternal mental health.",
    "url": "https://lotusrosecounseling.com/blog/",
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "@id": "https://lotusrosecounseling.com/#business",
      "name": "Lotus Rose Counseling"
    }
  })} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="blog-index-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">From Our Therapists</p>
      <h1>The Lotus Rose Blog</h1>
      <p class="blog-index-subtitle">Evidence-based insights on postpartum depression, trauma, grief, anxiety, and navigating the hardest chapters of life — from the therapists who treat them every day.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Featured Post -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/blog/postpartum-depression-vs-baby-blues/" class="featured-card">
        <span class="featured-badge">Featured</span>
        <span class="post-date">March 24, 2026</span>
        <h2>Postpartum Depression vs. Baby Blues: How to Tell the Difference</h2>
        <p class="featured-excerpt">Up to 80% of new mothers experience baby blues. But when does normal adjustment become something that needs professional help? Here's how to tell — and what to do about it.</p>
        <span class="read-more">Read Article →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Post Grid -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="grid-heading">All Articles</h2>
      <div class="post-grid">
        <a href="/blog/postpartum-depression-vs-baby-blues/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">March 24, 2026</span>
          <h3>Postpartum Depression vs. Baby Blues: How to Tell the Difference</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Up to 80% of new mothers experience baby blues. But when does it become something more?</p>
          <span class="read-more">Read Article →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>What to Expect in Your First EMDR Session</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Nervous about EMDR? Here's exactly what happens — from the moment you sit down to what you'll feel after.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>When Childhood Trauma Resurfaces in Motherhood</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">You came in for postpartum depression. But underneath, there's something older. Why motherhood triggers unprocessed childhood experiences.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>5 Things People Get Wrong About Therapy</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">It's not just talking. It's not a fast fix. And you don't need to be in crisis. Joy Bouchard debunks the most common misconceptions.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>EMDR vs. ART: Which Trauma Therapy Is Right for You?</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Both use eye movements. Both process trauma. But they work differently — and the right choice depends on your situation.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>The Mental Load of Motherhood: Why You're Exhausted</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">You're not lazy. You're carrying an invisible weight that nobody else in the house seems to notice.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>Infant Loss: Finding Your Way Through the Unthinkable</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Joy's most passionate area of work. How therapy holds space for grief that has no roadmap.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>How to Know If Your Therapist Is the Right Fit</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Joy's advice: call around, ask about 15-minute consultations, and don't commit until it feels right. Here's what to look for.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>What ART Therapy Actually Feels Like (From Someone Who's Done It)</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Accelerated Resolution Therapy sounds too good to be true — trauma relief in 1-5 sessions? Here's what actually happens.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>Co-Regulation: How to Stay Calm When Your Kids Can't</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Your toddler is melting down. Your nervous system is fried. A therapist explains co-regulation strategies that work in real chaos.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/coming-soon/" class="grid-card">
          <span class="post-date">Coming Soon</span>
          <h3>Why Therapy Takes Longer Than You Think (and Why That's Okay)</h3>
          <p class="grid-excerpt">Most clients work with their therapist for 6-12 months. Here's why — and what each phase of the journey looks like.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Coming Soon →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stay Connected -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <p class="section-label">Stay Connected</p>
      <h2>Follow Lotus Rose</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto 28px;">New articles, mental health tips, and updates from our practice — follow us on social media.</p>
      <div class="social-buttons">
        <a href="https://www.instagram.com/lotusrosecounseling/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="social-btn">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="20" rx="5" ry="5"/><path d="M16 11.37A4 4 0 1 1 12.63 8 4 4 0 0 1 16 11.37z"/><line x1="17.5" y1="6.5" x2="17.51" y2="6.5"/></svg>
          Instagram
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Talk to Someone?</h2>
      <p>Reading about mental health is a great start. When you're ready for the next step, we're here.</p>
      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Schedule Free Consultation</a>
        <a href="tel:+18016424244" class="btn-secondary">Call (801) 642-4244</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Blog Index Hero */
  .blog-index-hero {
    background: var(--blush-pink);
    padding: 60px 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .blog-index-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .blog-index-subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--text-medium);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Featured Card */
  .featured-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--warm-cream);
    border-left: 5px solid var(--peach-gold);
    border-radius: 0 16px 16px 0;
    padding: 40px 48px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    transition: all var(--transition-smooth);
  }
  .featured-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-medium);
    color: inherit;
  }
  .featured-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--btn-primary);
    color: var(--white);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    padding: 4px 14px;
    border-radius: 50px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .featured-card h2 {
    font-size: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .featured-excerpt {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  /* Post Grid */
  .grid-heading {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .post-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  .grid-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--white);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--peach-gold);
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: all var(--transition-smooth);
  }
  .grid-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-medium);
    color: inherit;
  }
  .grid-card h3 {
    font-size: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .grid-excerpt {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  /* Shared */
  .post-date {
    display: block;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-light);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .read-more {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--peach-gold);
  }

  /* Social */
  .social-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .social-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    border-radius: 50px;
    border: 2px solid var(--peach-gold);
    color: var(--peach-gold);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 15px;
    transition: all var(--transition-smooth);
  }
  .social-btn:hover {
    background: var(--peach-gold);
    color: var(--white);
  }
  .social-btn svg { stroke: currentColor; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .post-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .featured-card { padding: 28px 24px; }
    .featured-card h2 { font-size: 26px; }
    .social-buttons { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  }
</style>
